<br>
Just saying, with a 6 second cast time it would potentially reduce the chances of dying if pet dies before you think it will.<br>
<br>
I can get off a 6 second spell with a mob beating on me usually. But not 12 seconds. <br>
<br>
Also I'll give an example of where I think this is useful, something that happend to me the other day.<br>
<br>
Get agro by 2 mobs. Could have easily soloed either one, but sine one was on me, and one was one pet things were bleak and I had to gate, but in this same situation with quick cast I could have killed both.<br>
<br>
I could kite the other one around(have jboots). While pet dies fighting the second one. get a 6 second lead, could potentially have lost agro on second(could be good or bad thing), then cast a second pet. Just dont know many mobs I can get far enough ahead of to get a pet off with normal cast times.<br>
<br>
This is very what if, and few places, like maybe the grey, have the space to do it if you had to, but I think that quick cast might have some decent applications, just havent heard much talk about it. I just think it might keep you from having to zone in some situations where you pull 2 mobs(maybe more). and could just chain cast on multiple mobs, givin the right area.<br>
<br>
My whole point is, does anyone have quick cast, does it work, and have you found any real use for it?<br>
